frameDefinitions: A member or members of a Class have just been  mentioned or are present in the discourse setting and now a different instance  (or group of instances) of the same class is referred to.
The Authorities put a Prisoner in Prison as punishment for an Offense.
A speaker characterizes the intensity of an Attribute of an Entity by a Degree.
The size of an Entity is assessed in terms of the Degree by which it deviates from the norm.
This frame contains transparent nouns (and some adjectives) denoting quantities of a Mass or of Individuals.
This frame contains words that describe an Item's static position on a scale with respect to some property Variable.  '' 'Dried fruits are especially high in fibre, as are pulses.'
frameExamples: My husband left me for <t>another</t> woman -- and now wants to get back together again!
US Drug Researcher <t>Imprisoned</t> for FDA Fraud.
He found them in the <t>deluge</t> of papers on his desk.
Dried fruits are especially <t>high</t> in fibre, as are pulses.
listRoleDefinitions: The general category of entity which has been referred to.
The instance of the <fen>Class</fen> that is added to the <fen>Initial_set</fen> of entities in the <fen>Class</fen>.
The previously mentioned group of entities of the <fen>Class</fen>.
The person who is confined in a penal institution.
The <fen>Prison</fen>  within which the <fen>Prisoner</fen> comes to be confined.
The <fen>Authorities</fen> are the institution or actors carrying out the imprisonment.
The time when the imprisonment happens.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Prisoner</fen> is kept.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular gradable <fen>Attribute</fen> is appropriate and under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is under discussion.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the intensity of the <fen>Attribute</fen> from the norm or from the value for another <fen>Entity</fen>. This role is incorporated for each LU in this frame.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having  a particular <fen>Value</fen> for the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is has the <fen>Attribute</fen> to a given <fen>Degree</fen>.
The thing whose size is being considered.
The feature of an (actual or possible) <fen>Entity</fen> that is measured. In literal examples, it essentially must be size, or a word equivalent to size such as bulk.
The <fen>Quantity</fen>-denoting <t>Target</t> word.
A substance that is being quantified.
A collection of entities.
<fen>Item</fen> identifies the entity whose scalar property is specified.

<fen>Variable</fen> is the scalar property that the <fen>Item</fen> possesses.

<fex name='Item'>Soda</fex> is <t>high</t> <fex name='Variable'>in sugar</fex>.
The <fen>Value</fen> is the position or range of positions on the scale that the Item occupies.  This is normally implicit in the LU.
listRoleExamples: My Husband left me for another <fex>man</fex>!
A further five incursions <fex>over and above those noted for 1995</fex> took place in the first three months of 1996.
<fex>Man</fex> Falsely Imprisoned for 24 Years Seeks Damages
When she returned, <fex>the Chaoyang Town government authorities</fex> imprisoned her for 5 days.
The particles were smaller <fex>in size</fex> than expected .
A modicum <fex>of seepage on the floor</fex> is to be expected.
A number <fex>of concerned citizens</fex> have raised objections.
